WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.350 --> 00:00:04.530
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:10.900
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:11.470 --> 00:00:17.370
What he said in his final moments
drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:17.710 --> 00:00:19.640
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:20.170 --> 00:00:23.590
Go ahead. Find it!

7
00:00:23.590 --> 00:00:26.340
Everything is right where I left it!

8
00:00:26.840 --> 00:00:31.340
People set their sights on the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams.

9
00:00:31.950 --> 00:00:36.100
The world has truly entered
the Great Pirate Era!

10
00:00:37.890 --> 00:00:42.190
~The Dawn of an Adventure~

11
00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:41.650
This is a small seaport village.

12
00:00:42.190 --> 00:00:46.440
And at that port, a pirate ship has been
anchored for just over a year.

13
00:00:46.440 --> 00:00:51.170
An eastward wind passes
through this peaceful village...

14
00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.200
Hey, Luffy! What are you trying to do?!

15
00:00:56.570 --> 00:01:02.040
Monkey D. Luffy
Village Boy

16
00:00:56.790 --> 00:01:00.290
I've had it! I'm not a little kid anymore!

17
00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:02.040
I'm gonna prove it to you!

18
00:01:04.130 --> 00:01:07.880
Get on with it already...
whatever it is you're up to!

19
00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:11.840
Ouch!

20
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:14.390
You idiot! What'd you do that for?!

21
00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:15.930
Guys! A toast!

22
00:01:17.560 --> 00:01:21.940
To Luffy's guts and to another
successful voyage!

23
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:25.440
Ah, it didn't hurt one bit!

24
00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:27.730
Liar. You can't pull dumb stunts like that.

25
00:01:27.730 --> 00:01:28.940
I'm not lying!

26
00:01:28.940 --> 00:01:31.780
I'm not scared of getting hurt!

27
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:34.160
So, take me with you when you set sail!

28
00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:35.950
I wanna be a pirate too!

29
00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:39.950
Like you'd ever make it as a pirate!

30
00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:43.580
"Red-Haired" Shanks
Pirate Captain

31
00:01:40.370 --> 00:01:43.580
There's no use for a pirate
that sinks like an anchor!

32
00:01:43.580 --> 00:01:46.380
I'll be just fine if I don't fall overboard!

33
00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.710
And I'm good at fighting too!

34
00:01:48.710 --> 00:01:53.470
I've been training, so now
my punches are like pistols!

35
00:01:53.470 --> 00:01:54.800
Pistols?

36
00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:56.180
Oh, really?

37
00:01:56.180 --> 00:01:57.810
What's that supposed to mean?!

38
00:01:58.470 --> 00:01:59.180
Luffy!

39
00:01:59.180 --> 00:02:01.730
You're getting so worked up!

40
00:02:01.730 --> 00:02:04.020
Loosen up and have some fun!

41
00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:06.730
Yeah, that's what being a pirate's all about!

42
00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:09.110
The sea is boundless!

43
00:02:09.110 --> 00:02:11.570
There are tons of islands to explore!

44
00:02:11.570 --> 00:02:13.200
It's all about freedom!

45
00:02:14.660 --> 00:02:17.990
Guys, stop filling his head with nonsense.

46
00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:19.330
But it's all true!

47
00:02:19.330 --> 00:02:20.040
– Right?!
– Right?!

48
00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:23.460
C'mon, Chief, why not
take him on just one trip?

49
00:02:23.460 --> 00:02:24.960
I'd second that.

50
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:28.250
Sure, but one of you stays behind.

51
00:02:28.250 --> 00:02:31.420
Good chat, kid! Let's drink!

52
00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:32.970
Weren't you on my side?!

53
00:02:32.970 --> 00:02:35.930
Really, you're just too young, kid.

54
00:02:35.930 --> 00:02:38.930
Maybe I'll give you a chance
in about ten years!

55
00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:40.140
Shanks, you big jerk!

56
00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:41.680
I'm not a little kid!

57
00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:43.060
Hey, now. Simmer down.

58
00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:44.350
Here, have some juice.

59
00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:46.160
Oh! Thanks!

60
00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:49.730
See?! You are just a kid! Hilarious!

61
00:02:49.730 --> 00:02:51.480
No fair, Shanks!

62
00:02:52.490 --> 00:02:54.400
I'm so sick of this!

63
00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:57.910
Luffy, try to understand
where the chief is coming from.

64
00:02:57.910 --> 00:02:58.870
The first mate!

65
00:02:59.830 --> 00:03:03.330
The reality is, he's the head of a pirate crew.

66
00:03:03.330 --> 00:03:07.250
He knows better than anybody
how tough and dangerous pirating can be.

67
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:08.380
You get it?

68
00:03:08.380 --> 00:03:11.800
He's not trying to dash your hopes.

69
00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.210
No, I don't get it!

70
00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:16.590
Shanks just likes making fun of me!

71
00:03:16.590 --> 00:03:17.720
Look, an anchor!

72
00:03:17.720 --> 00:03:18.510
See?!

73
00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:20.930
I see you're having fun as usual.

74
00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:24.640
Yeah, I just love teasing this kid.

75
00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:27.270
Luffy, would you like something to eat too?

76
00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:29.860
Yeah! Put it on my treasure tab!

77
00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:31.650
The treasure tab again?

78
00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:33.900
That's fraud, you know?

79
00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:34.650
No, it's not!

80
00:03:34.650 --> 00:03:38.530
I'll pay her back once I become
a pirate and find some treasure!

81
00:03:39.370 --> 00:03:40.740
I'm counting on it.

82
00:03:42.790 --> 00:03:43.830
Shanks.

83
00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:44.790
What's up?

84
00:03:44.790 --> 00:03:47.500
How much longer are you
gonna stay in this village?

85
00:03:47.500 --> 00:03:48.620
Let's see...

86
00:03:48.620 --> 00:03:54.510
After a couple more voyages, we'll leave
this village for good and head north.

87
00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:58.220
A couple more voyages, huh...?

88
00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:04.020
So I gotta learn to swim before you leave!

89
00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:05.600
Sure thing.

90
00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:06.850
Knock yourself out.

91
00:04:11.650 --> 00:04:13.400
Excuse us.

92
00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:15.990
So, these are "pirates."

93
00:04:15.990 --> 00:04:17.950
Looks like a sorry bunch to me.

94
00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:29.330
We're mountain bandits,

95
00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:32.340
but we ain't here to bust up the place.

96
00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:33.840
Sell us some booze.

97
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.000
My apologies.

98
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:37.470
I just ran out of alcohol.

99
00:04:38.550 --> 00:04:40.970
Then what are these pirates drinking?

100
00:04:40.970 --> 00:04:42.600
Water?

101
00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:46.180
I'm afraid I served the last of it to them.

102
00:04:46.180 --> 00:04:48.350
I feel bad.

103
00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:52.230
Looks like we drank the whole place dry.

104
00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:53.150
Sorry!

105
00:04:54.070 --> 00:04:55.570
You can have this.

106
00:04:55.570 --> 00:04:57.400
It hasn't been opened yet.

107
00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:06.870
Hey, wise guy.

108
00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:09.910
What do you take me for?

109
00:05:09.910 --> 00:05:13.250
One bottle ain't even enough for a nightcap!

110
00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:16.800
The floor's all wet!

111
00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:18.090
Take a look.

112
00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.930
My head's worth eight million berries.

113
00:05:21.470 --> 00:05:26.260
I've killed fifty-six people,
all of 'em comedians like you.

114
00:05:26.260 --> 00:05:28.560
You'd better watch yourself.

115
00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:32.520
But we're mountain folk and you're seafarers;
I doubt we'll see each other again.

116
00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:36.980
Sorry about the mess, Makino.

117
00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:38.480
Do you have a rag?

118
00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.360
No! Leave that to me!

119
00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:50.660
Seems you like to clean.

120
00:05:50.660 --> 00:05:53.500
Maybe you'll find this more fulfilling.

121
00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:06.600
Later, cowards!

122
00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:15.400
Captain, are you all right?

123
00:06:15.400 --> 00:06:17.270
Yeah. No worries.

124
00:06:20.940 --> 00:06:23.320
Talk about lame, Chief!

125
00:06:23.320 --> 00:06:24.990
He got you good!

126
00:06:26.950 --> 00:06:28.620
Why are you laughing?!

127
00:06:28.620 --> 00:06:29.490
– Huh?
– Oh...

128
00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:31.540
That was so uncool!

129
00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:33.410
Why didn't you fight back?!

130
00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:38.540
You can't call yourself a man or a pirate
if you laugh after something like that!

131
00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:44.680
I get where you're coming from,
but he only got some booze on me.

132
00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:46.940
It's nothing worth getting mad over.

133
00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:51.020
Hey, wait, Luffy.

134
00:06:51.020 --> 00:06:53.480
Whatever! I don't wanna be a coward like you!

135
00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:01.860
His arm stretched!

136
00:07:01.860 --> 00:07:03.530
H-He didn't...!

137
00:07:03.530 --> 00:07:05.110
What's going on?!

138
00:07:05.110 --> 00:07:05.820
It's gone!

139
00:07:05.820 --> 00:07:07.030
– What?!
– What?!

140
00:07:07.030 --> 00:07:09.620
The Gum-Gum Fruit we stole
off that enemy vessel!

141
00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:13.500
Luffy! Please tell me
you didn't eat a fruit like this!

142
00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:14.830
I-I did...

143
00:07:14.830 --> 00:07:16.370
It tasted really bad.

144
00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:17.790
That was the Gum-Gum Fruit!

145
00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:20.800
It's a rare treasure of the sea
known as a devil fruit!

146
00:07:20.800 --> 00:07:25.760
You gain a rubber body after eating it,
but you lose the ability to swim for life!

147
00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:28.090
What?! No way!

148
00:07:28.090 --> 00:07:31.430
You dumbass!

149
00:07:34.390 --> 00:07:36.730
Gimme a fish, fish shop guy!

150
00:07:36.730 --> 00:07:38.060
Hey, Luffy!

151
00:07:38.060 --> 00:07:41.400
I heard they sailed off without you again!

152
00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:42.360
I don't mind!

153
00:07:42.360 --> 00:07:48.700
Becoming a rubber man is way cooler
than going on some dumb trip.

154
00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:54.250
It's been a while since the captain
and his crew set out to sea.

155
00:07:54.660 --> 00:07:56.290
I bet you miss them.

156
00:07:56.290 --> 00:07:59.130
No way! They're still not off the hook!

157
00:07:59.130 --> 00:08:03.170
I can't believe I thought Shanks
and his crew were awesome pirates.

158
00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:04.460
Really?

159
00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:08.970
I think it's much cooler to shrug it off and laugh
after someone humiliates you like that.

160
00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:11.140
Makino, you just don't get it.

161
00:08:11.140 --> 00:08:13.760
There are times when a man's gotta fight.

162
00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:15.730
I guess I don't understand.

163
00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:17.890
Hate to intrude.

164
00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:21.560
Those damn pirates ain't here today, huh?

165
00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:24.690
We were in the area,
so we decided to drop by.

166
00:08:30.410 --> 00:08:32.030
Why are you standing there?!

167
00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:33.740
Booze! Now!

168
00:08:37.370 --> 00:08:38.620
Mayor, we have a problem!

169
00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:40.420
What's wrong, Makino?

170
00:08:40.790 --> 00:08:43.250
Luffy's in trouble with the mountain bandits!

171
00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:46.710
Let go! Dammit!

172
00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:46.710
Weird body ya got here...

173
00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:50.010
Apologize already!

174
00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:52.470
What kind of creature is he?

175
00:08:51.090 --> 00:08:52.470
You dumb jerk!

176
00:08:56.310 --> 00:08:58.600
Dammit! You're gonna pay!

177
00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:01.650
He might fetch a good price.

178
00:09:03.900 --> 00:09:05.360
How stubborn.

179
00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:06.360
Brat!

180
00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:11.280
Did I say something to offend you?

181
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.660
You did! Now apologize!

182
00:09:13.660 --> 00:09:15.200
Get your foot off of me!

183
00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:17.370
Let the boy go!

184
00:09:18.330 --> 00:09:19.250
I beg you!

185
00:09:20.210 --> 00:09:24.090
I have no intention of fighting you.
If you allow it, I'll even pay you!

186
00:09:24.090 --> 00:09:27.300
Spare the boy's life!

187
00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:31.470
Leave it to a senior citizen
to know the ways of the world.

188
00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:33.930
But no.

189
00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:34.720
What?

190
00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:36.810
It's too late for that now,

191
00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:39.520
not after he's pissed me off.

192
00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:40.640
No...

193
00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:45.560
I'm fed up with this
rubber runt messing with me!

194
00:09:45.560 --> 00:09:49.400
You're the bad guys here, you mountain apes!

195
00:09:50.820 --> 00:09:52.700
Forget selling him.

196
00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:54.200
Let's just kill him!

197
00:09:55.160 --> 00:09:55.830
Luffy!

198
00:09:55.830 --> 00:09:57.700
Please! Let him go!

199
00:10:00.960 --> 00:10:03.620
No one came to greet us at the port.

200
00:10:05.670 --> 00:10:07.500
So, this is why.

201
00:10:08.710 --> 00:10:10.510
If it isn't those mountain bandits.

202
00:10:10.510 --> 00:10:11.920
Captain!

203
00:10:12.260 --> 00:10:16.800
Luffy, I thought your punches
were as strong as pistols.

204
00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:18.760
Shut up!

205
00:10:18.760 --> 00:10:21.390
So you pirates are still here, huh?

206
00:10:23.890 --> 00:10:26.400
You'd best leave before you get hurt.

207
00:10:26.400 --> 00:10:30.110
Any closer and you're dead meat, coward!

208
00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:34.070
What are you, deaf?

209
00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:35.950
I'll blow your head off!

210
00:10:38.410 --> 00:10:41.910
You've drawn your pistol,
so put your life on the line.

211
00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:43.620
Huh? The hell do you mean?

212
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:47.840
I'm saying those are for more
than just threatening someone.

213
00:10:58.470 --> 00:11:00.260
N-Now you've done it!

214
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.140
These bastards fight dirty!

215
00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:03.430
"Dirty"?

216
00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:05.310
Cut the crap.

217
00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:07.610
You think you're dealing with saints?

218
00:11:08.310 --> 00:11:12.070
You're looking at pirates!

219
00:11:12.070 --> 00:11:15.530
Shut up! This is none of your
damn business anyway!

220
00:11:15.530 --> 00:11:17.530
Listen, bandits.

221
00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:21.330
Whether I'm doused in alcohol
or covered in food,

222
00:11:21.330 --> 00:11:24.250
most of the time, I'll just laugh it off.

223
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:25.870
But know this!

224
00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:29.080
No matter the reason...

225
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:32.770
if you hurt my friends, you'll pay dearly!

226
00:11:34.260 --> 00:11:35.930
Shanks...

227
00:11:37.130 --> 00:11:38.760
Pay dearly, huh?!

228
00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:41.890
Lousy pirates! Kill 'em, men!

229
00:11:46.640 --> 00:11:48.940
I'll handle this. Piece of cake.

230
00:11:50.270 --> 00:11:52.110
Come on! Bring it!

231
00:11:52.980 --> 00:11:54.490
That burns!

232
00:12:01.410 --> 00:12:03.790
Don't get cocky, bandit.

233
00:12:05.370 --> 00:12:09.210
If you wanna fight us,
at least bring a battleship.

234
00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:11.540
So strong!

235
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:13.460
Unbelievable...

236
00:12:13.460 --> 00:12:17.170
Wait! Hold on! The kid attacked us!

237
00:12:17.170 --> 00:12:19.550
You're a wanted man, aren't you?

238
00:12:22.010 --> 00:12:23.640
A smokescreen!

239
00:12:23.640 --> 00:12:24.720
Come with me, brat!

240
00:12:24.720 --> 00:12:26.020
Let me go! Let me go!

241
00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:29.020
Luffy!

242
00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:31.690
Crap! I let my guard down!
He got Luffy! What do we do, guys?!

243
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:34.020
Quit freakin' the hell out, Chief!

244
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:36.570
If we all look, we'll find him in no time!

245
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:39.360
I can't believe this guy...

246
00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.200
I made a clean getaway!

247
00:12:43.200 --> 00:12:46.160
I got no use for you anymore!

248
00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:47.660
You bastard–

249
00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:50.580
So long!

250
00:12:51.040 --> 00:12:52.670
Dammit! Dammit!

251
00:12:52.670 --> 00:12:56.710
I couldn't land a single hit on those scumbags!

252
00:12:56.710 --> 00:12:59.300
Dammit! Dammit!

253
00:13:01.640 --> 00:13:04.310
You see the looks on those pirates' faces?!

254
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:07.600
Pirates ain't nothin' but cowards.
All bark and no bite.

255
00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:07.600
Cut it out!

256
00:13:07.600 --> 00:13:09.810
Stop making fun of Shanks and his crew!

257
00:13:09.810 --> 00:13:10.940
Calm down, Luffy!

258
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:15.860
Stop making fun of Shanks and his crew!

259
00:13:23.240 --> 00:13:24.450
Stupid brat.

260
00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:31.580
Wh-What the hell?!

261
00:13:34.790 --> 00:13:35.840
Help!

262
00:13:38.920 --> 00:13:40.760
It's gonna eat me!

263
00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:43.180
Help!

264
00:13:57.610 --> 00:13:59.150
Shanks...

265
00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:08.200
Get lost!

266
00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:32.680
I'm in your debt, Luffy...

267
00:14:33.230 --> 00:14:35.480
Makino told me everything.

268
00:14:36.110 --> 00:14:39.150
You stood up for us.

269
00:14:39.980 --> 00:14:41.900
C'mon, don't cry!

270
00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:43.110
You're a man, right?

271
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:47.120
But... Shanks...

272
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:50.240
Your arm!

273
00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:56.080
It's only an arm. No big deal.

274
00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:58.630
I'm just glad you're not hurt.

275
00:15:08.850 --> 00:15:12.520
Luffy finally understood the reason
Shanks never took him on a voyage.

276
00:15:12.520 --> 00:15:15.810
The sea was dangerous,
and he was powerless.

277
00:15:15.810 --> 00:15:19.310
But more importantly,
he discovered Shanks' greatness.

278
00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:24.280
He aspired to become a man like him one day.

279
00:15:27.360 --> 00:15:30.620
Shanks, you're not coming back?

280
00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:31.660
Nah.

281
00:15:31.660 --> 00:15:34.960
We were able to stay awhile,
but it's time to part ways.

282
00:15:35.710 --> 00:15:36.620
Right.

283
00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:38.920
I'm not gonna ask you to take me this time.

284
00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:42.380
I've decided to become a pirate on my own!

285
00:15:42.380 --> 00:15:44.470
I wasn't gonna take you anyway!

286
00:15:45.130 --> 00:15:47.720
You'll never make it as a pirate!

287
00:15:47.720 --> 00:15:48.890
Will too!

288
00:15:48.890 --> 00:15:52.890
Someday, I'm gonna gather a crew
every bit as good as yours.

289
00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:55.060
We'll find the world's greatest treasure...

290
00:15:55.390 --> 00:15:57.900
and then I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

291
00:15:59.310 --> 00:16:00.810
Oh?

292
00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:03.030
You're gonna surpass us, huh?

293
00:16:04.940 --> 00:16:06.030
In that case...

294
00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:12.370
I'll leave this hat with you.

295
00:16:18.790 --> 00:16:21.250
It means a lot to me.

296
00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:25.980
Come bring it back to me someday...

297
00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:28.760
once you've become a great pirate!

298
00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:33.640
He's got quite a future.

299
00:16:33.640 --> 00:16:37.560
Yeah, he's exactly like the kid I used to be.

300
00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:40.600
Set sail!

301
00:16:42.020 --> 00:16:47.780
The boy's adventure would begin
a decade later from this very port.

302
00:16:49.610 --> 00:16:52.700
Ten Years Later

303
00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:55.370
Well, Mayor, he's finally off.

304
00:16:55.370 --> 00:16:58.910
He's disgracing our village
by becoming a pirate!

305
00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:02.500
What a nice day to set sail!

306
00:17:08.590 --> 00:17:10.130
What the...?

307
00:17:11.340 --> 00:17:15.100
If it isn't the Lord of the Coast.
You don't know who you're messing with.

308
00:17:15.100 --> 00:17:17.980
Check out this technique
ten years in the making!

309
00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:23.270
Gum-Gum...

310
00:17:25.070 --> 00:17:27.070
Pistol!

311
00:17:36.870 --> 00:17:39.250
That'll teach you! Damn fish!

312
00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:48.420
Alright! Let's go!

313
00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:50.010
I'm gonna be...

314
00:17:50.010 --> 00:17:52.720
King of the Pirates!
